nodes.body:
This is about functions of a scalar argument, hence `deriv` rather than `fderiv`; so it should not go in the `fderiv` file but rather in `Analysis.Calculus.Deriv.Mul`, somewhere close to the existing lemma `HasDerivAt.finset_prod`. Here's a one-line proof of (a generalisation of) your lemma using that existing one:

```lean
import Mathlib

variable {ùïú : Type*} [NontriviallyNormedField ùïú] 
  {Œπ : Type*} [DecidableEq Œπ] {ùî∏' : Type*} [NormedCommRing ùî∏'] [NormedAlgebra ùïú ùî∏']
  {u : Finset Œπ} {f : Œπ ‚Üí ùïú ‚Üí ùî∏'} 

theorem DifferentiableAt.finset_prod (hd : ‚àÄ i ‚àà u, DifferentiableAt ùïú (f i) s) :
    DifferentiableAt ùïú (‚àè i ‚àà u, f i ¬∑) s := 
  (HasDerivAt.finset_prod (fun i hi ‚Ü¶ DifferentiableAt.hasDerivAt (hd i hi))).differentiableAt
```
Oh thank you very much thats much cleaner!
Can you add the ‚ÄúDifferentiableWithinAt‚Äù version to complete the set?

```suggestion

    (fun i hi ‚Ü¶ DifferentiableWithinAt.hasDerivWithinAt (hd i hi x hx))).differentiableWithinAt
```

